## MPLAB Harmony Graphics Suite is extensive!

#### Support for multiple display modules

The Suite contains support for various display sizes including:
- [wvga](\ref vector_mat)
- [wqvga](\ref image_mat)
- [qvga](\ref cv_mat)
- and more.

Each display timing can be hand-tuned by display manager.

#### Support for various display controllers

The Suite operates on common display controllers including:
- [ssd1963](\ref vector_mat)
- [ssd1953](\ref vector_mat)
- [ili9488](\ref vector_mat)

#### Extending MPLAB Harmony Graphics Suite

The Suite can be used with its existing display and touch controllers integrated with the Suire or extended to use third-party external touch and display controllers.

## Code once, run anywhere!

With Microchip PIC32 and SAM devices, MPLAB Harmony Graphics Suite supports a board range of design needs to meet and scale to market requirements.

Each MPLAB Harmony Graphics Suite installation comes with a comprehensive list of example applications :
 - a getting started application (named `legato_quickstart`) for showing a quick easy UI with touch capability.
 - a asset flashing application (named `legato_flash`) for external flash loading of assets.
 - a cooking applicaiton (named `legato_cooker`) to demonstrate.

